Package voltage.core

Class VoltageKeyPressInfo

java.lang.Object
voltage.core.VoltageKeyPressInfo
public class VoltageKeyPressInfo
extends java.lang.Object
VoltageKeyPressInfo provides information about a key-press event, including the key code of the key that was pressed, the character for that key (if valid), various helper functions to identify specialized key presses like escape, return, etc., and information about what modifier keys were down during the key press (shift, alt, etc.) A VoltageKeyPressInfo object gets passed as the 'object' parameter to Notify() during a Key_Press notification.

    • GetCharacter

      public int GetCharacter()
      returns the actual character typed ('r', 'R', etc.) as an integer. Differs from key codes, which correspond to a particular key, so 'r' and 'R' have the same key code value but different characters, for instance. Not meaningful if IsNonCharacterKeyCode() returns true.

    • IsNonCharacterKeyCode
